051f7230-d71f-4f76-9f50-c15acc65ad0d.do_description: To make the output, you have to...place the input grid in the top left 3x3. Then, reflect the top left 3x3 and place it in the top right 3x3. Now, reflect the top left and right 3x3 and place in the bottom left and right 3x3.
051f7230-d71f-4f76-9f50-c15acc65ad0d.see_description: In the input, you should see... a 3x3 grid with red blue and green colors.

7205a1f8-a911-40e3-94a7-ebefefe4d6cd.do_description: To make the output, you have to...place the original 3x3 grid in the upper left corner. Then the 3 remaining corners are simply mirrors of the original box pattern.
7205a1f8-a911-40e3-94a7-ebefefe4d6cd.grid_description: The output grid size...will be 6x6 so it can hold four 3x3 grids within it.
7205a1f8-a911-40e3-94a7-ebefefe4d6cd.see_description: In the input, you should see...a 3x3 grid with red, blue, black and green boxes.

732574d6-89e2-4164-b701-d75cabc82e4e.do_description: To make the output, you have to... make the top and bottom row all green. Make rows 2 and 5 all red with black as the first and last block. Make 2 2x2 blue squares in rows 3 and 4 with a 2x2 black square in the middle.
732574d6-89e2-4164-b701-d75cabc82e4e.grid_description: The output grid size... should be 6x6
732574d6-89e2-4164-b701-d75cabc82e4e.see_description: In the input, you should see... 3 green blocks in the top row, 2 red blocks in the second row, and 2 blue blocks in the third row.
